The article discusses the Obama administration's efforts to increase travel and tourism in the United States. It highlights the importance of the travel and tourism industry to the US economy and the potential for job creation. The article mentions various initiatives undertaken by the government, including the creation of a National Travel and Tourism Strategy, an international travel promotion campaign, and partnerships with local tourism leaders. It also discusses efforts to streamline the visa process, enhance the traveler experience at US airports, and provide information and data on public lands. Additionally, the article mentions initiatives to expand foreign language services, provide job opportunities for youth, support small businesses in the travel and tourism industry, and increase distribution of the "America the Beautiful" pass. Overall, the article emphasizes the importance of travel and tourism to the US economy and the government's commitment to promoting and facilitating travel to the United States.